::AxisBindingNotFoundError
  |~~ Axis-operand (`source` / `docs` / `examples`) could not find a `BindStep` for the requested binding name across loaded modules. ~~|
  {:qlang/kind :tag}

::DocsSubjectNotKeywordOrTagError
  |~~ `docs` requires a Keyword (`:foo`) or TagKeyword (`::Foo`) subject. ~~|
  {:qlang/kind :tag}

::ExamplesSubjectNotKeywordOrTagError
  |~~ `examples` requires a Keyword (`:foo`) or TagKeyword (`::Foo`) subject. ~~|
  {:qlang/kind :tag}

::SourceSubjectNotKeywordOrTagError
  |~~ `source` requires a Keyword (`:foo`) or TagKeyword (`::Foo`) subject. ~~|
  {:qlang/kind :tag}

|~ ──────────────── Projection (`/key`) throws ──────────────── ~|

::ProjectionFieldNotOnValueClassError
  |~~ Projection segment is not a publicly-projectable field on the value-class subject (Quote / Doc / …). ~~|
  {:qlang/kind :tag}

::ProjectionIndexOutOfBoundsError
  |~~ Projection `/n` — the integer index resolves outside the Vec subject's `[0, length)` range. ~~|
  {:qlang/kind :tag}

::ProjectionKeyNotInMapError
  |~~ Projection `/key` — the named key is absent from the Map subject (strict-miss). Use `at(:key)` for null-coalescing access. ~~|
  {:qlang/kind :tag}

::ProjectionSubjectNotMapError
  |~~ Projection `/key` requires a Map, Vec, or value-class subject; null subject and other shapes lift to this error. ~~|
  {:qlang/kind :tag}

::ProjectionVecKeyNotIntegerError
  |~~ Projection segment is a non-numeric string but the subject is a Vec — Vec indices must be integer offsets. ~~|
  {:qlang/kind :tag}

|~ ──────────────── Combinator track-dispatch throws ──────────────── ~|

::DistributeSubjectNotVecError
  |~~ Distribute combinator (`*`) — subject must be a Vec for per-element forking. ~~|
  {:qlang/kind :tag}

::MergeSubjectNotVecError
  |~~ Merge combinator (`>>`) — subject must be a Vec for one-level flattening. ~~|
  {:qlang/kind :tag}

|~ ──────────────── Tag-binding (::tag / ::conduit) throws ──────────────── ~|

::TagBindingHasNoConstructorError
  |~~ Tag-binding has no registered constructor — `:qlang/impl` is missing or wrong-shaped (expected a primitive Keyword or a Quote-impl body). The user-supplied payload is captured on the descriptor as `:payloadValue` / `:payloadType`; the actual `:qlang/impl` value as `:actualValue` / `:actualType`; the expected slot shape as `:expectedType [:keyword :quote]`. ~~|
  {:qlang/kind :tag}

::TaggedLitNotTagBindingError
  |~~ `::tag` constructor invocation failed — the env binding under `::tag` is not a tag-binding descriptor Map. ~~|
  {:qlang/kind :tag}

::TaggedLitTagNotFoundError
  |~~ `::tag` constructor invocation failed — the tag is not a registered tag-binding in env. ~~|
  {:qlang/kind :tag}

::ConduitArityMismatchError
  |~~ Conduit invocation supplied a captured-arg count different from the conduit's declared parameter list. ~~|
  {:qlang/kind :tag}

::ConduitBodyMissingSourceError
  |~~ `makeConduit` refuses a body AST that has no `.text` source slice — `printValue` round-trip would otherwise emit a non-parseable placeholder. ~~|
  {:qlang/kind :tag}

::ConduitParameterNoCapturedArgsError
  |~~ Conduit-parameter proxies are nullary — passing captured arguments to a parameter reference raises this error. ~~|
  {:qlang/kind :tag}

|~ ──────────────── Identifier-lookup + effect-laundering throws ──────────────── ~|

::EffectLaunderingAtBindStepParseError
  |~~ BindStep declaration body references an `@`-effectful identifier, but the binding name itself is not `@`-prefixed — laundering caught at parse time. ~~|
  {:qlang/kind :tag}

::ApplyToNonFunctionError
  |~~ Identifier resolves to a non-function value — captured arguments cannot be applied. ~~|
  {:qlang/kind :tag}

::EffectLaunderingAtCallError
  |~~ Identifier resolves to an `@`-effectful function, but the lookup name is not `@`-prefixed — laundering caught at the call site. ~~|
  {:qlang/kind :tag}

::UnresolvedIdentifierError
  |~~ Identifier lookup failed — no env binding under that name. ~~|
  {:qlang/kind :tag}

|~ ──────────────── Parser throws ──────────────── ~|

::ParseError
  |~~ Parser failure — source did not match the grammar. ~~|
  {:qlang/kind :tag}

|~ ──────────────── AST / value codec throws ──────────────── ~|

::AstMapKindUnknownError
  |~~ AST-Map → AST codec — `:qlang/kind` discriminator names a kind the codec does not know. ~~|
  {:qlang/kind :tag}

::AstMapMalformedError
  |~~ AST-Map → AST codec — input Map is malformed (missing required field, wrong shape). ~~|
  {:qlang/kind :tag}

::AstNodeTypeUnknownError
  |~~ AST → AST-Map codec — encountered an AST node whose `.type` is not in the codec's known shape table. ~~|
  {:qlang/kind :tag}

::MalformedTaggedJSONError
  |~~ `fromTaggedJSON` received a JSON shape it does not recognise as a tagged-value envelope. ~~|
  {:qlang/kind :tag}

::TaggedJSONUnencodableValueError
  |~~ `toTaggedJSON` cannot encode a function / conduit / snapshot value — use `serializeSession` for the binding-aware path. ~~|
  {:qlang/kind :tag}

|~ ──────────────── Evaluator + Rule 10 dispatch invariants ──────────────── ~|

::HigherOrderOpArityMismatchError
  |~~ Dispatch invariant — `higherOrderOp` impl received an unexpected captured-arg count. ~~|
  {:qlang/kind :tag}

::HigherOrderOpVariadicMissingCapturedError
  |~~ Dispatch invariant — `higherOrderOpVariadic` registration is missing the `captured` range argument. ~~|
  {:qlang/kind :tag}

::NullaryOpArgsProvidedError
  |~~ Dispatch invariant — nullary operand received captured arguments. ~~|
  {:qlang/kind :tag}

::OverloadedOpUnsupportedArityError
  |~~ Dispatch invariant — overloaded operand has no impl for the supplied captured-arg count. ~~|
  {:qlang/kind :tag}

::StateOpArityMismatchError
  |~~ Dispatch invariant — `stateOp` impl received an unexpected captured-arg count. ~~|
  {:qlang/kind :tag}

::StateOpVariadicMissingCapturedError
  |~~ Dispatch invariant — `stateOpVariadic` registration is missing the `captured` range argument. ~~|
  {:qlang/kind :tag}

::ValueOpArityMismatchError
  |~~ Dispatch invariant — `valueOp` impl received an unexpected captured-arg count for its declared arity. ~~|
  {:qlang/kind :tag}

::UnknownAstNodeTypeError
  |~~ Evaluator dispatch — encountered an AST node whose `.type` is not in `AST_NODE_EVALUATORS`. Runtime invariant violation, never reaches user code. ~~|
  {:qlang/kind :tag}

::UnknownCombinatorKindError
  |~~ Combinator dispatch — encountered a combinator kind not in `COMBINATOR_EVALUATORS`. Runtime invariant violation. ~~|
  {:qlang/kind :tag}

::Rule10ArityOverflowError
  |~~ Rule 10 — operand call supplied more captured arguments than the operand's declared maximum arity. ~~|
  {:qlang/kind :tag}

|~ ──────────────── Primitive-registry invariants ──────────────── ~|

::PrimitiveKeyAlreadyBoundError
  |~~ Primitive registry — two runtime modules tried to bind the same primitive name. ~~|
  {:qlang/kind :tag}

::PrimitiveKeyNotStringError
  |~~ Primitive registry — bind() received a non-string handle. ~~|
  {:qlang/kind :tag}

::PrimitiveKeyUnboundError
  |~~ Primitive registry — `:qlang/impl` handle on a descriptor Map points to a primitive that was never bound. ~~|
  {:qlang/kind :tag}

::PrimitiveRegistrySealedError
  |~~ Primitive registry — bind() called after the registry was sealed at langRuntime bootstrap. ~~|
  {:qlang/kind :tag}

|~ ──────────────── Session-codec throws ──────────────── ~|

::SessionBindingKindUnknownError
  |~~ Session deserialization — a binding entry carries an unknown `:kind`. ~~|
  {:qlang/kind :tag}

::SessionConduitSourceMissingError
  |~~ Session deserialization — a conduit binding entry has no `:source` to re-parse. ~~|
  {:qlang/kind :tag}

::SessionPayloadInvalidError
  |~~ Session deserialization — payload is malformed (missing required fields). ~~|
  {:qlang/kind :tag}

::SessionSchemaVersionMismatchError
  |~~ Session deserialization — payload `:schemaVersion` does not match the current SESSION_SCHEMA_VERSION. ~~|
  {:qlang/kind :tag}

|~ ──────────────── Render invariants ──────────────── ~|

::FunctionValueLeakedToPrintError
  |~~ `printValue` / `toPlain` invariant — a raw function value reached render. Wrap host operands in a descriptor Map carrying `:qlang/kind :builtin` and `:qlang/impl` when binding through `session.bind`. ~~|
  {:qlang/kind :tag}

|~ ──────────────── Misc throws ──────────────── ~|

::ConduitPayloadNotVecError
  |~~ `::conduit[…]` payload must be a Vec; a non-Vec payload raises this error. ~~|
  {:qlang/kind :tag}

::ConduitArityInvalidError
  |~~ `::conduit[…]` payload Vec must have either 2 elements (`[params body]`) or 3 elements (`[:self params body]`). ~~|
  {:qlang/kind :tag}

::ConduitBodyNotQuoteError
  |~~ `::conduit` body slot must be a Quote-value carrying the body source. ~~|
  {:qlang/kind :tag}

::ConduitParamNotKeywordError
  |~~ `::conduit` params Vec must contain only Keywords; one element is some other type. ~~|
  {:qlang/kind :tag}

::ConduitParamsNotVecError
  |~~ `::conduit` params slot must be a Vec of Keywords. ~~|
  {:qlang/kind :tag}

::ConduitSelfNameNotKeywordError
  |~~ `::conduit` self-name (3-element payload form) must be a Keyword. ~~|
  {:qlang/kind :tag}

::NullsFirstKeysNotComparableError
  |~~ Operands of `nullsFirst` are not pairwise-comparable scalars. ~~|
  {:qlang/kind :tag}

::NullsLastKeysNotComparableError
  |~~ Operands of `nullsLast` are not pairwise-comparable scalars. ~~|
  {:qlang/kind :tag}

::ReifyArityOverflowError
  |~~ `reify` accepts 0 or 1 captured arguments — `reify(:name)` resolves a named binding, bare `reify` describes pipeValue. ~~|
  {:qlang/kind :tag}
